{
  "stem": "20089.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were the kibbutz leader and probably about 30 or 40 children that were under him or her.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they lived in dormitories.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there were a few adults.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But when I first arrived, it was mainly just children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it's all very interesting, the story of these children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I didn't realize this until much later.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Jewish Agency-- because Israel was still Palestine, the Jewish Agency had sent their personnel to the camps to work with the children.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But before they sent them to the camps, they sent a lot of them to Poland and to Lithuania, where families had come-- had either survived and gone back to Poland-- but most of them that were in our camps were not so much survivors of the camps, but-- but people who had been driven by the-- the Poles out of Poland into Russia at the beginning of the war.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And fortunately, the Russians sent them to Siberia, because the Russians were not very pro-Jews and they thought that they might become spies.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So they sent them to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And most of these were the survivors of the Siberian camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And after the war, they came back to their old villages.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And of course, there was no one left.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so they either went to Germany as families-- but mostly the Jewish Agency couldn't take them as families.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So they came and took the children, with a promise to the parents that as soon as they had organized these children in the displaced persons camps, they would come back for the parents.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And so the parents allowed their children to be separated from them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And these were the children that we had at the Rosenheim camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
